history.content:
There is a data science decal called Practical Data Science Skills for Internships, and based off of the description, it seems very useful, practical, and would expand your skills.

https://decal.berkeley.edu/courses/4163

I am currently enrolled in CS61C and CS70, Which means that I need 4 more units to be full time. I am also waitlisted for CS160 and CS168, but I'm quite sure I probably won't get in since my place on the waitlist is > 100. What are some good decals to take, that are tech related or will allow me to expand some skills in CS? Or is there any other options apart from decals to obtain 4 units? I've completed all of my Humanities and Social Sciences breadth requirements plus my American Culture class, so those aren't an option. Thank you
history.subject: Advice on what to take together with CS61C and CS70? any good decals out there?
